06/06/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Democratic Party of Serbia (DSS) on Sunday (5 June) re-elected Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica as its leader. 
He was the sole candidate for the post. 
Addressing the party, he said his priorities include preserving the federal union with Montenegro, working for eventual EU integration, and resolving the Kosovo issue.
In other news, Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic says Belgrade is ready for a compromise agreement with Pristina regarding Kosovo's status. 
In an interview with the Austrian news agency APA on Friday (3 June), Draskovic said the Serbian government has demonstrated its willingness for compromise with its "more than autonomy, less than independence" stance. 
He added that it is now Pristina's turn. 
(Tanjug, B92 - 05/06/05; Tanjug - 04/06/06; Beta - 03/06/05)
